member.remarks:
To get an absolute URL from an attribute that may be a relative URL, prefix the key with abs, 
which is a shortcut to the {@link #absUrl} method. 
E.g.: string url = a.attr("abs:href");

member.summary:
Get an absolute URL from a URL attribute that may be relative (i.e. an <a href> or 
<img src>).
E.g.: String absUrl = linkEl.absUrl("href");

            Creates a new IConnection to a URL. Use to fetch and parse a HTML page.
            Use examples:


Document doc = NSoupClient.Connect("http://example.com").UserAgent("Mozilla").Data("name", "jsoup").Get();

Document doc = NSoupClient.Connect("http://example.com").Cookie("auth", "token").Post();

members.member:
If the stack contains an element with this tag's name, pop up the stack to remove the first occurrence. If not
found, skips.

@param endTag

